CONTENT: Hello Manish! Thank you so much for the reply! Will get back to you once I've finished the project!

Happy Sat Shreya and thanks for your interest in hushh. You’ve got an amazing profile and come with a strong reference from Avaneesh who we just hired into hushh.  If you’re interested in pursuing a internship or full time job with hushh you should complete this project and share your design document, your code and explanation on what you’ve build and a 5 min demo video that shows what you have built.  Project hushhproto: Build a mobile app for iOS or Android that has a simple search engine interface (think google) or a search bot (thank chatGPT or bard) with a simple mobile UI that runs against 3-5 valuable personal data takeouts of yours (think gmail, LinkedIn, google maps, google chrome search and browsing history, Instagram, Facebook, WhatsApp, etc). This search and chat interface should work against atleast 3 valuable large personal datasets of yours. You can use the data takeout api and service available by Google, Facebook, Instagram, Apple, LinkedIn to take all your personal data out of these companies database. They all offer this for free and you can read up more about how to do this using google or chatGPT. If you aren’t comfortable with mobile app development you could do the same as a developer focused api that a front end developer can use to emulate the same behavior.  Please note You are free to use any of the latest technologies including chatGPT, GitHub Copilot, or Replit to build this prototype including using opensource LLMs and cutting edge vector databases like pinecone. The demo should highlight how this search or chatbot is useful to you as a user. Remember You are the target user for this prototype so make sure whatever you build is something you’ll plan to use and enjoy using as a user.   Once you’re done with this project and have sent all the above, please use the links below to schedule a formal interview with me and my leadership team.  Schedule time with Manish via - https://calendly.com/hushh/30min   and also setup time with Justin via https://calendly.com/justin_donaldson/30min  and Sunaz https://calendly.com/sunaz/intro_meeting so we can all quickly chat with you and evaluate how and when you can come help us on the hushh mission.  Cheers! Manish

CONTENT: Hello Shreya,  Hope you are doing well and are in the best of your spirits.    As you are kindly aware that Employee Burnout directly impacts an organization’s top and bottom lines by raising costs, decreasing productivity, and reducing client satisfaction. It is the leading cause of employee turnover and decreased productivity from top level managers to general workers.  Resiliency Program is a 360-degree wellness solution to reduce/ eliminate Burnout Syndrome. CONVERSATION TITLE: Drexel University - Survey on National Culture & Technology
CONTENT:
Dear Mr. Akurathi,

 

I am Sumit Ganguli, and I am pursuing a Doctorate Program at the LeBow College of Business, Drexel University, Philadelphia, PA, USA. I am conducting my dissertation under the guidance of Professor Daniel Tzabbar, Ph.D. 

 

My research is to study the impact of National Culture on the Culture of Innovation within technology firms and the Innovative Outputs from these firms. We will also measure the effect of Innovation on the Economic Values of these technology companies. We would like to examine this hypothesis on Indian and Israeli IT companies. 

 

As a part of this research, we would like to survey senior leaders like you, from information technology companies in Israel and India. We are confident that the survey will have a direct impact on the process of innovation and give us more insight into the firm-level culture within information technology companies in Israel and India. 

 

We would be much obliged if you could kindly complete this survey, and you can access it by clicking on this link. 


Take the Survey!


We thank you for your time and we would like to commit to you, that this survey will be conducted with integrity and confidentiality. The results of this survey will be used only for academic purposes and will not be disclosed to anyone. We have also received the statutory IRB approval for this survey. Please do read the instructions before you start the survey. 

 

Regards, 

 

Sumit Ganguli 

DBA Program at LeBow College of Business, 

Drexel University
